  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Empowering Women Through Civil Society Actors in Bangladesh</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The intervention will be the disbursement of sub -grants to target Civil Society Actors (CSAs) that will provide them the resources and opportunity to support the target women workers combined with capacity strengthening support in terms of organisational development, thematic awareness and technical knowledge relevant to the target sectors. To support effective use of the sub -grants, CSA sub -grantees will be supported with up to date and relevant sectoral knowledge through research and support for opportunities to engage with target sector policy and decision makers such as government regulators and service providers or employers and industry representatives. Similarly sub -grantees will be supported to strengthen the capacity of women workers in the target sectors through learning events, training and coaching approaches combined with awareness raising on key issues at the individual, community and workplace levels and opportunities to engage and interact directly with policy and decision makers within their sectors such as employers and managers.</narrative>
  </description>
